<threat_model>
**Attack Surface:** New Redis stream consumer, submission callback hook point, feature extraction on user-submitted code.
**Threats:**
- Cross-tenant data leak through analysis events (HIGH) — events must carry organization_id and consumer must filter by it
- DoS via maliciously structured source code crashing the extractor (MEDIUM)
- Redis stream unbounded growth (LOW) — needs capped consumer lag monitoring
**Mitigations:**
- All analysis queries filter by organization_id (tenant isolation)
- Feature extractor runs in spawn_blocking with timeout and size limits
- Redis stream trimmed to MAXLEN ~10000 entries
- Shadow pipeline failures are logged and swallowed — never propagate to the caller
**Block on:** HIGH — cross-tenant data leak must be prevented by design
</threat_model>

